<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-499-275  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 499 275.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Oct 1 1990 v9 n21 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Atwood named GCN Govt. Exec of Year. (Department of Defense deputysecretary Donald J. Atwood honored by Government Computer News)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseAchievements and AwardsManagementGovernment AgencyGovernment Computer News (Periodical).andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Donald J. Atwood. (portrait)Person:    Atwood, Donald J. (achievements and awards).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Atwood Named GCN Govt.andP;  Exec of YearandM;Donald J. Atwood, deputy secretary of Defense, has been named the 1990Government Computer News government Executive of the Year.andM;Atwood, who was vice chairman of General Motors before being named deputysecretary in January 1989, was honored for his role in strengthening theDefense Department's IRM programs and curbing fraud, waste and abuse.andM;At its annual banquet last month, GCN also honored five agencies for theirefforts to improve services.andM;DOD's Directorate of Engineering and Construction was cited for developingthe Construction Criteria Base, a compact disk system for distributinginformation on the design and construction of buildings and civil works.andM;The Environmental Protection Agency's Program Systems Division was recognizedfor its Systems Modernization Initiative.andP;  The four-part program was designedto improve systems development, ease technology transfer, develop integratedapplications and manage contractors.andM;The U.S.andP;  Geological Survey's Telecommunications Branch was honored forexcellence in planning, management and operations.andP;  The branch has usedstatistical analysis and modeling for assessing throughput, usage and chargesfor its Geonet network and FTS 2000 to cut costs and improve services.andM;The Social Security Administration's Division of Database Systems was citedfor its Database Integration Program that helped SSA field offices accessdata and support applications in an on-line environment.andM;The Transportation Department's computer center was recognized for changingfrom an old-fashioned ADP center to a customer-oriented service operation.andM;In addition, the Interagency Working Group for Data Management for GlobalChange was honored for its efforts to help scientists obtain research data.andO;Member agencies include the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration,the National science Foundation, the Energy Department, NASA, the U.S.andO;Geological Survey, EPA, Navy and the State Department.andO;</TEXT></DOC>